The '''white-headed buffalo weaver''' or '''white-faced buffalo-weaver''' ('''''Dinemellia dinemelli''''') is a species of [[passerine]] [[bird]] in the family [[Ploceidae]] native to [[East Africa]].{{r|BirdLife}} The buffalo part of its name derives from its habit of following the [[African buffalo]], feeding on disturbed insects.{{r|oise}} Two subspecies are recognized.

==Taxonomy==
The white-headed buffalo weaver was first described by the German [[Natural history|naturalist]] [[Eduard Rüppell]] in 1845.{{r|ibc}}

===Subspecies===
Two subspecies of the white-headed buffalo weaver are now recognized.{{r|ibc}}
